{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1999,"text":"Well, we all need a reason to wake up."},{"time":6898,"text":"For me, it just took 11,000 volts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11068,"text":"I know you're too polite to ask,"},{"time":12766,"text":"so I will tell you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15354,"text":"One night, sophomore year of college,"},{"time":17601,"text":"just back from Thanksgiving holiday,"},{"time":21323,"text":"a few of my friends and I\nwere horsing around,"},{"time":23999,"text":"and we decided to climb atop\na parked commuter train."},{"time":28167,"text":"It was just sitting there,\nwith the wires that run overhead."},{"time":31305,"text":"Somehow, that seemed\nlike a great idea at the time."},{"time":34804,"text":"We'd certainly done stupider things."},{"time":38270,"text":"I scurried up the ladder on the back,"},{"time":41315,"text":"and when I stood up,"},{"time":43061,"text":"the electrical current entered my arm,"},{"time":46667,"text":"blew down and out my feet,\nand that was that."},{"time":51699,"text":"Would you believe that watch still works?"},{"time":56216,"text":"Takes a licking!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57447,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58502,"text":"My father wears it now in solidarity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63295,"text":"That night began my formal relationship\nwith death -- my death --"},{"time":69342,"text":"and it also began\nmy long run as a patient."},{"time":73174,"text":"It's a good word."},{"time":74352,"text":"It means one who suffers."},{"time":76825,"text":"So I guess we're all patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79607,"text":"Now, the American health care system"},{"time":81997,"text":"has more than its fair share\nof dysfunction --"},{"time":85142,"text":"to match its brilliance, to be sure."},{"time":87750,"text":"I'm a physician now,\na hospice and palliative medicine doc,"},{"time":92226,"text":"so I've seen care from both sides."},{"time":95076,"text":"And believe me: almost everyone\nwho goes into healthcare"},{"time":98999,"text":"really means well -- I mean, truly."},{"time":102874,"text":"But we who work in it\nare also unwitting agents"},{"time":106831,"text":"for a system that too often\ndoes not serve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111999,"text":"Why?"},{"time":113624,"text":"Well, there's actually a pretty easy\nanswer to that question,"},{"time":117029,"text":"and it explains a lot:"},{"time":119301,"text":"because healthcare was designed\nwith diseases, not people, at its center."},{"time":126419,"text":"Which is to say, of course,\nit was badly designed."},{"time":130158,"text":"And nowhere are the effects\nof bad design more heartbreaking"},{"time":136234,"text":"or the opportunity\nfor good design more compelling"},{"time":139593,"text":"than at the end of life,"},{"time":141758,"text":"where things are so distilled\nand concentrated."},{"time":146234,"text":"There are no do-overs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150073,"text":"My purpose today is\nto reach out across disciplines"},{"time":154588,"text":"and invite design thinking\ninto this big conversation."},{"time":159495,"text":"That is, to bring intention and creativity"},{"time":164876,"text":"to the experience of dying."},{"time":169235,"text":"We have a monumental\nopportunity in front of us,"},{"time":173292,"text":"before one of the few universal issues"},{"time":177657,"text":"as individuals as well as a civil society:"},{"time":180991,"text":"to rethink and redesign how it is we die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187489,"text":"So let's begin at the end."},{"time":191611,"text":"For most people, the scariest thing\nabout death isn't being dead,"},{"time":195570,"text":"it's dying, suffering."},{"time":197809,"text":"It's a key distinction."},{"time":200461,"text":"To get underneath this,\nit can be very helpful"},{"time":202653,"text":"to tease out suffering\nwhich is necessary as it is,"},{"time":207031,"text":"from suffering we can change."},{"time":210317,"text":"The former is a natural,\nessential part of life, part of the deal,"},{"time":215577,"text":"and to this we are called\nto make space, adjust, grow."},{"time":223013,"text":"It can be really good\nto realize forces larger than ourselves."},{"time":229098,"text":"They bring proportionality,"},{"time":232246,"text":"like a cosmic right-sizing."},{"time":236779,"text":"After my limbs were gone,"},{"time":239237,"text":"that loss, for example,\nbecame fact, fixed --"},{"time":243847,"text":"necessarily part of my life,"},{"time":247184,"text":"and I learned that I could no more\nreject this fact than reject myself."},{"time":255173,"text":"It took me a while,\nbut I learned it eventually."},{"time":258572,"text":"Now, another great thing\nabout necessary suffering"},{"time":261040,"text":"is that it is the very thing"},{"time":264572,"text":"that unites caregiver and care receiver --"},{"time":269999,"text":"human beings."},{"time":273089,"text":"This, we are finally realizing,\nis where healing happens."},{"time":277673,"text":"Yes, compassion -- literally,\nas we learned yesterday --"},{"time":281217,"text":"suffering together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284672,"text":"Now, on the systems side,\non the other hand,"},{"time":288034,"text":"so much of the suffering\nis unnecessary, invented."},{"time":292376,"text":"It serves no good purpose."},{"time":294674,"text":"But the good news is,\nsince this brand of suffering is made up,"},{"time":298999,"text":"well, we can change it."},{"time":301681,"text":"How we die is indeed\nsomething we can affect."},{"time":306446,"text":"Making the system sensitive\nto this fundamental distinction"},{"time":310523,"text":"between necessary\nand unnecessary suffering"},{"time":313999,"text":"gives us our first of three\ndesign cues for the day."},{"time":318299,"text":"After all, our role as caregivers,\nas people who care,"},{"time":322852,"text":"is to relieve suffering --\nnot add to the pile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330292,"text":"True to the tenets of palliative care,"},{"time":332187,"text":"I function as something\nof a reflective advocate,"},{"time":335884,"text":"as much as prescribing physician."},{"time":339177,"text":"Quick aside: palliative care -- a very\nimportant field but poorly understood --"},{"time":345222,"text":"while it includes, it is not\nlimited to end of life care."},{"time":348200,"text":"It is not limited to hospice."},{"time":350811,"text":"It's simply about comfort\nand living well at any stage."},{"time":354999,"text":"So please know that you don't\nhave to be dying anytime soon"},{"time":358062,"text":"to benefit from palliative care."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361450,"text":"Now, let me introduce you to Frank."},{"time":365768,"text":"Sort of makes this point."},{"time":367007,"text":"I've been seeing Frank now for years."},{"time":369061,"text":"He's living with advancing prostate cancer\non top of long-standing HIV."},{"time":374197,"text":"We work on his bone pain and his fatigue,"},{"time":376207,"text":"but most of the time we spend thinking\nout loud together about his life --"},{"time":380945,"text":"really, about our lives."},{"time":383071,"text":"In this way, Frank grieves."},{"time":385207,"text":"In this way, he keeps up with\nhis losses as they roll in,"},{"time":389010,"text":"so that he's ready to take in\nthe next moment."},{"time":393524,"text":"Loss is one thing,\nbut regret, quite another."},{"time":399243,"text":"Frank has always been an adventurer --"},{"time":401224,"text":"he looks like something\nout of a Norman Rockwell painting --"},{"time":404089,"text":"and no fan of regret."},{"time":406566,"text":"So it wasn't surprising\nwhen he came into clinic one day,"},{"time":409271,"text":"saying he wanted to raft\ndown the Colorado River."},{"time":413142,"text":"Was this a good idea?"},{"time":415268,"text":"With all the risks to his safety\nand his health, some would say no."},{"time":419496,"text":"Many did, but he went for it,\nwhile he still could."},{"time":423999,"text":"It was a glorious, marvelous trip:"},{"time":428928,"text":"freezing water, blistering dry heat,\nscorpions, snakes,"},{"time":434274,"text":"wildlife howling off the flaming walls\nof the Grand Canyon --"},{"time":439729,"text":"all the glorious side of the world\nbeyond our control."},{"time":444492,"text":"Frank's decision, while maybe dramatic,"},{"time":446406,"text":"is exactly the kind\nso many of us would make,"},{"time":448717,"text":"if we only had the support to figure out\nwhat is best for ourselves over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457291,"text":"So much of what we're talking about today\nis a shift in perspective."},{"time":462723,"text":"After my accident,\nwhen I went back to college,"},{"time":464999,"text":"I changed my major to art history."},{"time":468095,"text":"Studying visual art, I figured\nI'd learn something about how to see --"},{"time":473705,"text":"a really potent lesson\nfor a kid who couldn't change"},{"time":477103,"text":"so much of what he was seeing."},{"time":480602,"text":"Perspective, that kind of alchemy\nwe humans get to play with,"},{"time":484364,"text":"turning anguish into a flower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489999,"text":"Flash forward: now I work\nat an amazing place in San Francisco"},{"time":493815,"text":"called the Zen Hospice Project,"},{"time":496078,"text":"where we have a little ritual\nthat helps with this shift in perspective."},{"time":500405,"text":"When one of our residents dies,"},{"time":503490,"text":"the mortuary men come, and as we're\nwheeling the body out through the garden,"},{"time":507984,"text":"heading for the gate, we pause."},{"time":510038,"text":"Anyone who wants --"},{"time":512247,"text":"fellow residents, family,\nnurses, volunteers,"},{"time":514995,"text":"the hearse drivers too, now --"},{"time":517463,"text":"shares a story or a song or silence,"},{"time":521914,"text":"as we sprinkle the body\nwith flower petals."},{"time":525282,"text":"It takes a few minutes;"},{"time":527610,"text":"it's a sweet, simple parting image\nto usher in grief with warmth,"},{"time":532999,"text":"rather than repugnance."},{"time":536060,"text":"Contrast that with the typical experience\nin the hospital setting,"},{"time":541130,"text":"much like this -- floodlit room\nlined with tubes and beeping machines"},{"time":546018,"text":"and blinking lights that don't stop\neven when the patient's life has."},{"time":551419,"text":"Cleaning crew swoops in,\nthe body's whisked away,"},{"time":554469,"text":"and it all feels as though that person\nhad never really existed."},{"time":561070,"text":"Well-intended, of course,\nin the name of sterility,"},{"time":563717,"text":"but hospitals tend to assault our senses,"},{"time":567237,"text":"and the most we might hope for\nwithin those walls is numbness --"},{"time":572765,"text":"anesthetic, literally\nthe opposite of aesthetic."},{"time":578499,"text":"I revere hospitals for what they can do;\nI am alive because of them."},{"time":584096,"text":"But we ask too much of our hospitals."},{"time":587436,"text":"They are places for acute trauma\nand treatable illness."},{"time":591053,"text":"They are no place to live and die;\nthat's not what they were designed for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598078,"text":"Now mind you -- I am not\ngiving up on the notion"},{"time":600402,"text":"that our institutions\ncan become more humane."},{"time":604057,"text":"Beauty can be found anywhere."},{"time":609092,"text":"I spent a few months in a burn unit"},{"time":611388,"text":"at St. Barnabas Hospital\nin Livingston, New Jersey,"},{"time":614160,"text":"where I got really\ngreat care at every turn,"},{"time":618341,"text":"including good\npalliative care for my pain."},{"time":621415,"text":"And one night, it began to snow outside."},{"time":625426,"text":"I remember my nurses\ncomplaining about driving through it."},{"time":630103,"text":"And there was no window in my room,"},{"time":632311,"text":"but it was great to just imagine it\ncoming down all sticky."},{"time":637299,"text":"Next day, one of my nurses\nsmuggled in a snowball for me."},{"time":641257,"text":"She brought it in to the unit."},{"time":644731,"text":"I cannot tell you the rapture I felt\nholding that in my hand,"},{"time":650163,"text":"and the coldness dripping\nonto my burning skin;"},{"time":653236,"text":"the miracle of it all,"},{"time":655570,"text":"the fascination as I watched it melt\nand turn into water."},{"time":663293,"text":"In that moment,"},{"time":665448,"text":"just being any part of this planet\nin this universe mattered more to me"},{"time":669960,"text":"than whether I lived or died."},{"time":672083,"text":"That little snowball packed\nall the inspiration I needed"},{"time":675230,"text":"to both try to live\nand be OK if I did not."},{"time":679176,"text":"In a hospital, that's a stolen moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684356,"text":"In my work over the years,\nI've known many people"},{"time":687769,"text":"who were ready to go, ready to die."},{"time":691192,"text":"Not because they had found\nsome final peace or transcendence,"},{"time":695999,"text":"but because they were so repulsed\nby what their lives had become --"},{"time":702553,"text":"in a word, cut off, or ugly."},{"time":711394,"text":"There are already record numbers of us\nliving with chronic and terminal illness,"},{"time":717504,"text":"and into ever older age."},{"time":719947,"text":"And we are nowhere near ready\nor prepared for this silver tsunami."},{"time":727335,"text":"We need an infrastructure\ndynamic enough to handle"},{"time":730620,"text":"these seismic shifts in our population."},{"time":735637,"text":"Now is the time to create\nsomething new, something vital."},{"time":738681,"text":"I know we can because we have to."},{"time":741065,"text":"The alternative is just unacceptable."},{"time":743651,"text":"And the key ingredients are known:"},{"time":745557,"text":"policy, education and training,"},{"time":749255,"text":"systems, bricks and mortar."},{"time":752642,"text":"We have tons of input\nfor designers of all stripes to work with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757123,"text":"We know, for example, from research"},{"time":759028,"text":"what's most important to people\nwho are closer to death:"},{"time":762538,"text":"comfort; feeling unburdened\nand unburdening to those they love;"},{"time":769527,"text":"existential peace; and a sense\nof wonderment and spirituality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776896,"text":"Over Zen Hospice's nearly 30 years,"},{"time":780678,"text":"we've learned much more\nfrom our residents in subtle detail."},{"time":785662,"text":"Little things aren't so little."},{"time":789499,"text":"Take Janette."},{"time":790697,"text":"She finds it harder to breathe\none day to the next due to ALS."},{"time":794208,"text":"Well, guess what?"},{"time":796121,"text":"She wants to start smoking again --"},{"time":799523,"text":"and French cigarettes, if you please."},{"time":804786,"text":"Not out of some self-destructive bent,"},{"time":807033,"text":"but to feel her lungs filled\nwhile she has them."},{"time":812786,"text":"Priorities change."},{"time":815556,"text":"Or Kate -- she just wants to know"},{"time":818051,"text":"her dog Austin is lying\nat the foot of her bed,"},{"time":822110,"text":"his cold muzzle against her dry skin,"},{"time":825851,"text":"instead of more chemotherapy\ncoursing through her veins --"},{"time":828598,"text":"she's done that."},{"time":830849,"text":"Sensuous, aesthetic gratification,\nwhere in a moment, in an instant,"},{"time":835889,"text":"we are rewarded for just being."},{"time":843373,"text":"So much of it comes down to\nloving our time by way of the senses,"},{"time":847679,"text":"by way of the body -- the very thing\ndoing the living and the dying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854258,"text":"Probably the most poignant room"},{"time":855841,"text":"in the Zen Hospice guest house\nis our kitchen,"},{"time":858118,"text":"which is a little strange when you realize"},{"time":860179,"text":"that so many of our residents\ncan eat very little, if anything at all."},{"time":864016,"text":"But we realize we are providing\nsustenance on several levels:"},{"time":869910,"text":"smell, a symbolic plane."},{"time":874356,"text":"Seriously, with all the heavy-duty stuff\nhappening under our roof,"},{"time":879297,"text":"one of the most tried and true\ninterventions we know of,"},{"time":883055,"text":"is to bake cookies."},{"time":898144,"text":"As long as we have our senses --"},{"time":899772,"text":"even just one --"},{"time":901808,"text":"we have at least\nthe possibility of accessing"},{"time":905241,"text":"what makes us feel human, connected."},{"time":910999,"text":"Imagine the ripples of this notion"},{"time":913809,"text":"for the millions of people\nliving and dying with dementia."},{"time":917554,"text":"Primal sensorial delights that say\nthe things we don't have words for,"},{"time":921843,"text":"impulses that make us stay present --"},{"time":924741,"text":"no need for a past or a future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930280,"text":"So, if teasing unnecessary suffering out\nof the system was our first design cue,"},{"time":938559,"text":"then tending to dignity\nby way of the senses,"},{"time":941287,"text":"by way of the body --\nthe aesthetic realm --"},{"time":945103,"text":"is design cue number two."},{"time":947944,"text":"Now this gets us quickly to the third\nand final bit for today;"},{"time":951774,"text":"namely, we need to lift our sights,\nto set our sights on well-being,"},{"time":958662,"text":"so that life and health and healthcare"},{"time":961999,"text":"can become about making life\nmore wonderful,"},{"time":964408,"text":"rather than just less horrible."},{"time":968196,"text":"Beneficence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970999,"text":"Here, this gets right at the distinction"},{"time":973158,"text":"between a disease-centered and a patient-\nor human-centered model of care,"},{"time":978316,"text":"and here is where caring\nbecomes a creative, generative,"},{"time":981801,"text":"even playful act."},{"time":984657,"text":"\"Play\" may sound like a funny word here."},{"time":987687,"text":"But it is also one of our\nhighest forms of adaptation."},{"time":990615,"text":"Consider every major compulsory effort\nit takes to be human."},{"time":995298,"text":"The need for food has birthed cuisine."},{"time":997825,"text":"The need for shelter\nhas given rise to architecture."},{"time":1000437,"text":"The need for cover, fashion."},{"time":1002667,"text":"And for being subjected to the clock,"},{"time":1005422,"text":"well, we invented music."},{"time":1011766,"text":"So, since dying\nis a necessary part of life,"},{"time":1014999,"text":"what might we create with this fact?"},{"time":1020054,"text":"By \"play\" I am in no way suggesting\nwe take a light approach to dying"},{"time":1023454,"text":"or that we mandate\nany particular way of dying."},{"time":1026117,"text":"There are mountains of sorrow\nthat cannot move,"},{"time":1028999,"text":"and one way or another,\nwe will all kneel there."},{"time":1032999,"text":"Rather, I am asking that we make space --"},{"time":1036524,"text":"physical, psychic room, to allow life\nto play itself all the way out --"},{"time":1042291,"text":"so that rather than just\ngetting out of the way,"},{"time":1045672,"text":"aging and dying can become\na process of crescendo through to the end."},{"time":1052931,"text":"We can't solve for death."},{"time":1058283,"text":"I know some of you are working on this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060614,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1065003,"text":"Meanwhile, we can --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066839,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068879,"text":"We can design towards it."},{"time":1072042,"text":"Parts of me died early on,"},{"time":1073441,"text":"and that's something we can all say\none way or another."},{"time":1076583,"text":"I got to redesign my life\naround this fact,"},{"time":1079248,"text":"and I tell you it has been a liberation"},{"time":1082612,"text":"to realize you can always find\na shock of beauty or meaning"},{"time":1085791,"text":"in what life you have left,"},{"time":1088082,"text":"like that snowball lasting\nfor a perfect moment,"},{"time":1090870,"text":"all the while melting away."},{"time":1094700,"text":"If we love such moments ferociously,"},{"time":1100743,"text":"then maybe we can learn to live well --"},{"time":1103039,"text":"not in spite of death,"},{"time":1105150,"text":"but because of it."},{"time":1110520,"text":"Let death be what takes us,"},{"time":1112720,"text":"not lack of imagination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1116868,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1118044,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}